<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="157" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,153,863]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,801,827]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species name is derived from the Latin, 
<emphasis box="[858,954,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">galbinus</emphasis>
(= yellow) with a Latin adjective suffix, - 
<emphasis box="[151,199,838,863]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">inea</emphasis>
, referring to the yellowish white band on the forewing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
